## Folder Structure (apps/mobile/lib/)

```
core/
  config/         # AppConfig, environment flavors (dev/staging/prod)
  network/        # Dio instance, auth interceptor, 401 handler
  storage/        # SecureStorage wrapper (tokens), Hive (offline)
  security/       # Jailbreak detector, screenshot guard
  router/         # GoRouter, auth guard, role guard
  theme/          # AppTheme, AppColors, AppTypography, AppSpacing

features/
  auth/
    data/         # AuthRepository, AuthRemoteDataSource
    domain/       # AuthState, User model
    presentation/ # LoginScreen, MfaScreen, AuthNotifier (Riverpod)
  dashboard/
    data/
    domain/
    presentation/
  properties/
    data/
    domain/
    presentation/
  inventory/
    data/
    domain/
    presentation/
  settings/
    presentation/

shared/
  widgets/        # Reusable premium UI components
  extensions/     # Dart extensions
```

---

## Architecture Rules

### State Management
- Use **Riverpod** exclusively — no Provider, no BLoC, no setState in feature code
- Every feature has a `*Notifier` class extending `AsyncNotifier` or `Notifier`
- State classes use **Freezed** — immutable, with copyWith

### Data Layer
- Each feature has a `Repository` class that calls `RemoteDataSource`
- `RemoteDataSource` uses the shared Dio instance from `core/network/`
- Models use `freezed` + `json_serializable` — always generate with `build_runner`

### Navigation
- **GoRouter** only — no Navigator.push directly
- Auth guard: redirect to `/login` if no valid token
- Role guard: redirect to `/unauthorized` if role insufficient

### UI
- No business logic in widgets — widgets only call notifier methods and read state
- Shared components only in `shared/widgets/`
- Use `AppTheme`, `AppColors`, `AppTypography`, `AppSpacing` — no hardcoded colors or sizes

---

## API Integration

### Base URL
```dart
// From AppConfig — never hardcode
AppConfig.apiBaseUrl // e.g. http://10.0.2.2:3000/api (Android emulator)
                     // or https://api.vaulted.app (production)
```

### Authentication
- **Access Token**: stored in memory (Riverpod state) — never in SharedPreferences
- **Refresh Token**: stored in `flutter_secure_storage`
- On 401: Dio interceptor automatically calls `POST /auth/refresh`, retries original request
- On refresh failure: clear tokens, redirect to login

### Standard API Response format (from backend ResponseInterceptor)
```json
{ "success": true, "data": { ... } }
{ "success": false, "error": { "statusCode": 401, "message": "..." } }
```
Always unwrap `.data` field before passing to domain layer.

---

## Security Rules (MANDATORY)

1. **Tokens in memory or SecureStorage only** — never SharedPreferences, never logs
2. **Certificate pinning** with Dio — implement in `core/network/api_client.dart`
3. **Biometric re-auth** on app resume after 5 min background
4. **Screenshot blocked** on sensitive screens (item detail with valuations, auth screens)
5. **Jailbreak/root detection** on app start — warn user, optionally block
6. **No hardcoded secrets** — all config from AppConfig / flavors

---

## Naming Conventions

- Files: `snake_case.dart`
- Classes: `PascalCase`
- Riverpod providers: `camelCaseProvider` / `camelCaseNotifierProvider`
- Freezed models: `@freezed class ModelName with _$ModelName`
- Always run `dart fix --apply` after generating code

---

## Backend Endpoints Available

### Auth
```
POST /api/auth/register
POST /api/auth/login       → returns { accessToken, mfaRequired }
POST /api/auth/refresh     → reads httpOnly cookie
POST /api/auth/logout
POST /api/auth/mfa/setup   → returns { secret, qrCodeUrl }
POST /api/auth/mfa/verify  → returns { accessToken, mfaVerified: true }
```

### Properties
```
GET    /api/properties
POST   /api/properties
GET    /api/properties/:id
PUT    /api/properties/:id
DELETE /api/properties/:id
POST   /api/properties/:id/floors
POST   /api/properties/:id/floors/:floorId/rooms
```

### Inventory
```
GET    /api/items?propertyId=&category=&status=&q=&page=&limit=
POST   /api/items
GET    /api/items/:id
PUT    /api/items/:id
DELETE /api/items/:id
POST   /api/items/:id/move
POST   /api/items/:id/loan
GET    /api/items/:id/history
```

### Dashboard
```
GET /api/dashboard
```

### Users
```
POST   /api/users/invite
GET    /api/users
GET    /api/users/:id
PUT    /api/users/:id
DELETE /api/users/:id
```

### Media
```
POST   /api/media/upload   → multipart/form-data, field: "file"
DELETE /api/media/file?key=tenantId/uuid.ext
```

---

## Flutter Phases to Build (in order)

### Phase 1 — Auth screens
- LoginScreen: email + password form, handle mfaRequired flag
- MfaScreen: 6-digit TOTP input
- AuthNotifier: manages login flow, token storage, redirect
- GoRouter auth guard

### Phase 2 — Properties
- PropertiesListScreen: list of properties with PropertyCard widget
- PropertyDetailScreen: floors and rooms tree
- AddPropertyScreen: form with address fields
- PropertiesNotifier + PropertiesRepository

### Phase 3 — Inventory
- ItemsListScreen: filterable list with ItemCard, CategoryFilter, StatusBadge
- ItemDetailScreen: photos, attributes, valuation, QR code display
- AddItemScreen: full form with category selection
- QrScannerScreen: scan QR → navigate to item detail
- InventoryNotifier + InventoryRepository

### Phase 4 — Media
- ImagePickerWidget: camera + gallery, preview, upload progress
- Integrate into AddItemScreen and ItemDetailScreen
- CachedNetworkImage for displaying photos

### Phase 5 — Dashboard
- DashboardScreen: stats cards (total items, total valuation, items by status)
- PropertyCards on dashboard
- GlobalSearchScreen: search bar + filters

---

## DO NOT

- Do not modify anything in `apps/api/`
- Do not use `setState` for feature state — use Riverpod
- Do not hardcode colors, sizes, or API URLs
- Do not store tokens in SharedPreferences
- Do not call API directly from widgets — always through Repository
- Do not skip Freezed for data models

---

## Dart / Flutter Code Quality Rules (MANDATORY)

### Color opacity — ALWAYS use `.withValues(alpha:)`, NEVER `.withOpacity()`
```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
color: AppColors.accent.withValues(alpha: 0.6)
color: Colors.black.withValues(alpha: 0.3)

// ❌ WRONG — deprecated, causes precision loss
color: AppColors.accent.withOpacity(0.6)
color: Colors.black.withOpacity(0.3)
```

### Unused callback parameters — ALWAYS use `_` wildcard (Dart 3+), NEVER `__` or `___`
```dart
// ✅ CORRECT — Dart 3 allows multiple _ wildcards
errorBuilder: (_, _, _) => fallbackWidget,
error: (_, _) => const SizedBox.shrink(),

// ❌ WRONG — unnecessary_underscores lint error
errorBuilder: (_, __, ___) => fallbackWidget,
error: (_, __) => const SizedBox.shrink(),
```

### String interpolation — omit braces for simple identifiers
```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
'$itemCount item(s)'
'$roomName — detail'

// ❌ WRONG — unnecessary_brace_in_string_interps lint
'${itemCount} item(s)'
'${roomName} — detail'
```
Exception: braces ARE required for expressions, member access, or index access:
`'${item.name}'`, `'${list.length}'`, `'${map['key']}'`

### Generated files — never manually edit these
Files ending in `.g.dart` and `.freezed.dart` are auto-generated by build_runner.
Always run `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` after changing a model.
These files are excluded from `analysis_options.yaml` — do not add them to version control ignores.
